snippet: Days after the election, there are contradictory signals about which side has the upper hand in Thailand’s debilitating power struggle.
abstract: Petition to nullify Thailand's general election is rejected on procedural grounds by the country's ombudsman, setback for the opposition Democrat Party, which is allied with protesters trying to overthrow the government of Prime Min Yingluck Shinawatra.
lead_paragraph: Days after the election, there are contradictory signals about which side has the upper hand in Thailand’s debilitating power struggle.

headline.main: Petition to Nullify Thai Election Is Rejected in Setback for Opposition
